{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3600,"name":"","username":"franck22000","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/f/f4b2a3/{size}.png","created_at":"2014-12-13T16:46:58.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHello,\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI am a professional game developer and i am planning to release my game which has been approved on Steam Greenlight during the next year (i keep my project name secret for the moment on this forum).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI am very interested to use urho3D as a game engine base and expand it’s features. You guys are doing a great work \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/slight_smile.png?v=5\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI have some questions before making the switch !\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e1- Is there any automated way to generate the “include” folder when i am building the engine from the source ?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e2- I have noticed that the decals in the decals sample are not affected by lights and shadows. Is it possible to make them affected by the lighting ? Or is it planned ?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e3- Is there any roadmap for the engine or can you tell me which are the next big planned features ?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e4- What about the recast “detourcrowd” integration ? will it be finished soon or should i add this feature myself ?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThank you for your time and i am looking forward to discuss with you guys. \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/wink.png?v=5\" title=\":wink:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":wink:\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:01:58.722Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":1,"readers_count":0,"score":0.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":664,"topic_slug":"some-general-questions","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"